<p>Because strings must be written within quotes, JavaScript will misunderstand this string:</p>

<p><code>var y = "We are the so-called "Vikings" from the north."</code></p>

<p>
    The solution to avoid this problem, is to use the \ escape character. The backslash escape character turns special
    characters into string characters.
</p>

<p><strong>Escape Character Examples</strong></p>

<ul>
    <li>\' single quote</li>
    <li>\\ backslash</li>
    <li>\n new line</li>
    <li>\r carriage return</li>
    <li>\t tab</li>
    <li>\b backspace</li>
    <li>\f form feed</li>
</ul>

